        <abstract> 
<p>Thanks AdeC for great pleasure his new book [<hi rend="italic">Histoire des sciences</hi> (1873)] has given him. Comments on several of the essays.</p> 
            <p>When AdeC backs up Asa Gray in saying all instincts are congenital habits, CD must protest.</p> 
<p>Asks several questions about butterflies of the Alps discussed on p. 322 [of <hi rend="italic">Histoire</hi>].</p> 
        </abstract>
